President Obama has signed an emergency declaration for the State of New York in response to the conditions caused by Hurricane Irene. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to affected areas. FEMA is authorized to identify and provide necessary resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency, with 75 percent of funding coming from the federal government. Philip E. Parr has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.